Recently, tax authorities in India launched a large-scale and highly irregular investigation of Chinese companies. These enterprises included mobile companies such as OPPO, Xiaomi and OnePlus. On Thursday, Gao Feng, spokesperson for the Ministry of Commerce, said China hopes India can provide a fair, transparent and non-discriminatory environment for Chinese businesses. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Guan Xin analyzes India's actions that seem to benefit local competitors, but actually damage the image of the country and harm the investment environment.